text: Corey Michael Locke (born May 8, 1984) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey player. He played nine games in the National Hockey League (NHL). He played for the Montreal Canadiens, New York Rangers, and Ottawa Senators. He also played for TPS of the SM-liiga (SM-l). He was born in Newmarket, Ontario.
